latestPosts.caption:
Every day without Marshmellow is a reminder of how much I miss him. This photo is a bittersweet reminder of his presence, even though he’s not physically here. New York was the first time after his passing where I truly felt like my old self again, and I would like to think that he is here with me whenever I travel, sharing these experiences and making me feel his presence. I see signs of him along the way, and it’s like he’s always with me in spirit. I love you Marshmellow, more than words can say. I wish heaven had visiting hours, but until we reunite one day, you will always be loved and missed 💙

#mysoulmatedog #soulmatedog #mycuddlebug❤️ #myfurbabyboy #myfirstbaby❤️ #myfirstbabyboy💙 #alwaysyourmom #foreverlovedandmissed #foreverlovedneverforgotten #foreverlovedforevermissed #rainbowdogs #rainbowdog🌈 #rainbowbridgepets #rainbowbridgedog #rainbowbridgedogs🌈 #missingyouforever #imissmydogsomuch #imissmydoggy #imissmydoggie #theonethatmademeamom #dogmommas #dogmom🐾 #myheartwillneverbethesame #alwayswithme❤️ #alwaysbymyside♥️ #iloveyoualways❤️ #iloveyoualwaysandforever❤️ #alwaysbemybaby❤️ #alwaysgoingtobemybaby #reunitedoneday

After a rough few months dealing with depression and grieving, traveling to New York brought back my sparkle and joy that I had lost. This was the first time in a while that I felt genuinely happy and alive again. I saw signs and felt Marshmellow with me, reminding me of the bond that we have and that life is short and to live it to the fullest 💙🐾 This trip reignited my spark and I am forever grateful for our trip, it was very much needed. New York will always have a special place in my heart 💖
